# GNN Bot Detection Experiments

## ü§ñ Overview

This directory contains code and experiments related to implementing Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for **Node Classification**, specifically in the context of identifying suspicious users or bots within a social network graph.

The goal is to leverage the structural (graph) and feature information of users to classify them as either normal accounts or bots.

## üìÅ Directory Structure

| File/Folder | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| `README.md` | This file. |
| `Graph_Data_Prep.ipynb` | Code for preparing a **custom synthetic social graph** dataset, defining features, labels (normal vs. bot), and converting the structure into a PyTorch Geometric (PyG) `Data` object. |
| `Basic_GCN_Model.ipynb` | An example of training a **Simple Graph Convolutional Network (GCN)** model for node classification on a standard benchmark dataset (Cora). This serves as a foundational GNN implementation. |
| `1&2 images`

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup and Dependencies

This project relies on PyTorch and the PyTorch Geometric (PyG) library for efficient graph processing.

